  "license": "CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)",
  "instruction": "A population doubles every period. If P(0) = {a1} and the growth factor is r = {r}, find P({n_term}).",
  "params": {
    "a1": {
      "type": "int",
      "min": 1,
      "max": 5
    },
    "r": {
      "type": "int",
      "min": 2,
      "max": 3
    },
    "n_term": {
      "type": "int",
      "min": 3,
      "max": 6
    }
  },
  "answer_expr": "geomseq",
  "steps": [
    "Discrete growth model: P(t) = P(0) * r^t.",
    "P({n_term}) = {a1} * {r}^{n_term} = {a1} * {r_pow} = {answer_geomseq}."
  ],
  "tags": [
    "exponential-growth",
